pros:
steep learning curve but it all depends on the team; 
passionate young people for the most part;
exposure to various groups within operations across the globe;

cons:
unwillingness to invest in its people leading to a revolving door environment;
lack of clear direction due to change in management every few years;
few career path opportunities unless you have strong connections;
not offering competitive pay;

- Management layer usually not involved in keeping a high performing team and business development;
- Low performers are kept in the organization with no real improvement plan or acknowledgement of their flaws from the management team
- Always turning the 'blind eye' on what to really improve, that requires management decision (it always is someone else's fault, not ours); weak decision making process or accountability of changes needed to be made
